body:
Even when having #![feature(fs)] in the crate attributes, "use of unstable library feature 'fs'" is not silenced.  All other warnings I have in the crate attributes, like `#![feature(io)]`, are correctly silenced.

I am running using the nightly build as of 2/22/15 on Arch Linux.

My src/lib.rs:

``` Rust
#![feature(fs)]
#![feature(io)] 
#![allow(non_snake_case)]
#![allow(dead_code)]
pub mod gb_memory;
```

Warnings from terminal:

```
src/gb_memory.rs:1:5: 1:12 warning: use of unstable library feature 'fs'
src/gb_memory.rs:1 use std::fs;
                       ^~~~~~~
src/gb_memory.rs:1:5: 1:12 help: add #![feature(fs)] to the crate attributes to silence this warning
src/gb_memory.rs:1 use std::fs;
                       ^~~~~~~
src/gb_memory.rs:97:22: 97:36 warning: use of unstable library feature 'fs'
src/gb_memory.rs:97     let mut f = try!(fs::File::open(fileName)); 
                                         ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<std macros>:1:1: 6:57 note: in expansion of try!
src/gb_memory.rs:97:17: 97:48 note: expansion site
